On Friday evening, fire crews and SANParks managed to contain the blaze. CAPE TOWN - The Table Mountain National Park (TMNP) says various parts of Signal Hill are still smoldering, after a fire broke out in the area on Friday.On Friday evening, fire crews and SANParks managed to contain the blaze.Firefighters will remain on Signal Hill today in case of any flare-ups.TMNP fire manager Phillip Prince says: The fire is contained at this stage and it's under control. There will still be smoke coming from that area as there are logs smouldering. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)